com.siperian.sif.message.mrm

Class PreviewBvtResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.SiperianResponse
      • com.siperian.sif.message.mrm.PreviewBvtResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataProvider, RecordKeyProvider, Serializable

    public class PreviewBvtResponse
extends SiperianResponse
implements RecordKeyProvider, DataProvider

    Response to a PreviewBvtRequest. The Record object in the response includes BvtField objects for columns that are trust-enabled and Field objects for columns that are not trust-enabled. The BvtField object includes the rowid of the base object record that contributed to the field value.

    Usage Example: The following example shows how to print out the results in a PreviewBvtResponse: 

    
 // Construct the request
 PreviewBvtRequest request = new PreviewBvtRequest();
 ...
 PreviewBvtResponse response = (PreviewBvtResponse) sipClient.process (request);
 
 // Print the results
 System.out.println("BVT Record for rowid : " + response.getRecordKey().getRowid());
 for (Iterator iter=response.getRecord().getFields().iterator(); iter.hasNext();) {
     //iterate through record fields
     Object obj = iter.next();
     if (obj instanceof Field) {
         Field field = (Field) obj;
         System.out.println("Column " + field.getName() + " = " + field.getValue());
     }
     else if (obj instanceof BvtField) {
         BvtField field = (BvtField) obj;
         System.out.println("Column " + field.getName() + " = " + field.getValue() + " from base object record with rowid:" + field.getRowidLineage());
     }
 }
    See Also:
    PreviewBvtRequest, BvtField, Field, Serialized Form

    API Pair: PreviewBvtRequest

    API Group: Data Retrieval
